\fs18 \cf4 \cb31 \strokec4 It didn't matter if no one understood her. As long as she had music, that was enough. It didn't matter if no one ever talked to her first, either. She'd never expected them to anyway...\cb1 \
\cb31 Being surrounded by people made her so nervous that she fled the world, using delusions to fill the empty space it left behind. She was the master of her own tiny realm, setting up "keep out" warnings at the edges, then painting everything bright with music.\cb1 \
\cb31 "I'm not like them. I\'97I'm a lonely genius!"\cb1 \
\cb31 She puffed out her cheeks and quietly wiped away the lonely tear that slipped from the corner of her eye.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

