\fs18 \cf4 \cb31 \strokec4 "That kid's an odd one, always humming strange songs alone in the corner..."\cb1 \
\cb31 Having heard such remarks all her life, she stopped hoping for any other kind of judgment.\cb1 \
\cb31 Then, one warm and gentle afternoon, a dark-haired girl stretched her hand out like an angel.\cb1 \
\cb31 Ah... so she had always been seeking this sense of being understood. Always... waiting for someone she could call a friend.\cb1 \
\cb31 Even having grown accustomed to loneliness from endless practice, humans are still, in the end, social animals. That person lifted her out of damp, clinging solitude, and from then on, she had a shelter made of feathers.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

