\fs18 \cf4 \cb31 \strokec4 The stars were strung across the night like gas lamps lit at dusk.\cb1 \
\cb31 She imagined that somewhere in the vast galaxy, someone was driving a clattering electric tram, setting off from pale morning light and heading straight toward infinity.\cb1 \
\cb31 The passengers were all adorable little creatures like cats, dogs, and bunnies, and the conductor was fluent in the languages of deep-sea fish and owls.\cb1 \
\cb31 Leaving behind the rush of everyday life, stepping away from mundane routines\'97\cb1 \
\cb31 "If I could borrow the wings of the Angels of Delusion, maybe I could bring everyone into a world of music like this!"\cb1 \
\cb31 Surrounded by the sugary aroma of a scented candle, she stretched with a soft yawn, then wrote this romantic dream onto the sheet music.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

